    "long_instructions": "You're building a fitness app that tracks a user's daily step goal. Your app needs to remember how many steps the user is aiming for each day.\r\n\r\n## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Create a variable called `step_goal`.\r\n\r\n2. Assign it a number, like `8000` or `10000`.\r\n\r\n3. Use `print()` to show a message like `Your daily step goal is 10000 steps.`\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYou can use **commas** in a `print()` statement to combine text and variables. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\nprint(\"Name:\", first_name)\r\n```",
